# Benefits of this Approach

This structure is commonly used in real-world Terraform projects because it allows:

* environment-based deployments
* reusable infrastructure code
* easier configuration management
* cleaner Terraform projects
* reduced chances of accidental configuration changes

---

# Real-World Use Case

Using separate tfvars files is very common while managing:

* Development environments
* QA environments
* Staging environments
* Production environments

The same Terraform codebase can deploy completely different infrastructure just by changing the tfvars file passed during execution.

---

# Example Workflow

## Deploy Development Infrastructure

```bash id="h9wn0k"
terraform apply -var-file="dev.terraform.tfvars"
```

---

## Deploy Production Infrastructure

```bash id="gr4dyt"
terraform apply -var-file="prod.terraform.tfvars"
```
